                    .column.is-8.is-offset-1-desktop
                        .project-details__intro-text-wrapper
                            %p
                                A proposal to Ocean Spray that aimed to captivate the Puerto Rican market and position their Chilled Juice as the leading brand in its category. To get there, we built a strategy that brought together both online and offline channels, creating a seamless experience that reached consumers wherever they were.
                            %p
                                At the core of our approach was content that felt trustworthy, relatable, and exciting. We wanted people to genuinely connect with the product, so we focused on messaging that tapped into growing health trends in the market and highlighted the natural benefits of the product in a way that reflected Puerto Rican values and lifestyle. To amplify that, we proposed an influencer program built around authenticity, alongside a public relations push that helped build relationships with key media figures across the island.
                            %p
                                We also proposed bringing the brand to life through sampling events, giving consumers the chance to experience Ocean Spray Chilled Juice firsthand. Throughout every stage, we offered continuous performance tracking and refinement to keep the strategy sharp and effective, with the ultimate goal of establishing Ocean Spray Chilled Juice as the go-to choice in Puerto Rico in the chilled juice segment.
                            %p 
                                This project was developed in collaboration with two fellow designers.
        .project-details__gallery-wrapper
            .container
                .project-details__description-wrapper
                    .columns.is-variable.is-6
                        .column.is-4
                            %p.eyebrow Campaign Theme
                            %h2 Headline
                        .column.is-8
                            %p.projects__middle-text
                                For the headline, we went with "Sácale el jugo a tu bienestar." The phrase plays on the double meaning of juicing something and making the most out of it, which works perfectly in Spanish. In Puerto Rico, "sacarle el jugo a X" is a beloved expression that encourages people to embrace every moment, kind of like their own version of carpe diem. It felt like a natural fit for a product that's all about getting the most out of what you put into your body.
                = image_tag "https://nicolada-website.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/oc-bb-1.webp", loading: 'lazy'
                .project-details__objectives-wrapper
                    .columns.is-variable.is-6
                        .column.is-4
                            %p.eyebrow Strategy
                            %h2 Objectives
                        .column.is-8
                            .project-details_objectives
                                %h3 Positioning
                                %p Establish Ocean Spray as the leading wellness brand in the Puerto Rican market through a targeted communication plan that highlights the product's nutritional value and promotes a healthier lifestyle.
                            .project-details_objectives
                                %h3 Localization
                                %p Captivate Puerto Rican consumers by crafting a value proposition that speaks to local culture and values, building trust and fostering long-term relationships through a mix of traditional and digital channels.
                            .project-details_objectives
                                %h3 Trial & Awareness
                                %p Drive awareness of Ocean Spray's new chilled juice range by showcasing its flavors and nutritional benefits through a creative launch strategy designed to boost brand recognition and encourage consumers to try it for the first time.
                = image_tag "https://nicolada-website.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/oc-bb-2.webp", loading: 'lazy'
                .project-details__description-wrapper
                    .columns.is-variable.is-6
                        .column.is-3
                            %p.eyebrow Strategy
                            %h2 Offline Efforts
                        .column.is-8.is-offset-1
                            %p.projects__middle-text
                                Our offline strategy proposed meeting consumers where they already were. We suggested a range of point-of-purchase materials like stoppers, wobblers, danglers, and an endcap display to grab attention right at the shelf. We also proposed organizing sampling events to get the product directly into people's hands, with ongoing performance monitoring to make sure everything stayed on track.
